About Us
We are a leading provider of energy efficient, cutting edge equipment, instrumentation, and process control systems to the global mining industry. With companies in Brazil, Chile, Mexico and South Africa, Woodgrove has built a reputation based on quality, performance and safety. The company is entrepreneurial, dynamic and our team are driven to succeed. We are looking for likeminded individuals that want to be part of a transformational
Role Summary
This role is for a position within the Advanced Process Control (APC) department. The APC department works with mine sites around the world (both remotely and on site) to deploy and integrate optimization solutions for the benefit of clients and industry.
This role is ideal for someone who enjoys travelling and has an analytical mind.
Essential Responsibilities
Deployment and integration of "smart instruments" at client sites;
Deployment and integration of Advanced Regulatory Control applications;
Deployment and integration of Expert Systems;
Producing technical documentation (e.g. reports, manuals, specifications, drawings);
Managing existing support-contracts, attending to technical demands as they arise;
Conducting feasibility studies (with focus on instrumentation and control, operations optimisation);
Conducting data analysis;
R&D initiatives for developing innovative solutions for the mineral processing industry;
Process modeling and simulation
Qualifications/Requirements
3+ Years of experience in mineral processing (comminution, flotation, leaching, hydrometallurgy, etc.); Desirable but not mandatory.
Bachelor’s degree in Mineral Processing/Extractive Metallurgy/Chemical Engineering, or a related field.
Skills
Excellent written and oral communication skills.
International work experience would be beneficial, or the proven ability to work with different cultures on a technical project.
Start up and commissioning experience of mineral processing plants is highly desirable.
Experience working with control systems (ABB, DeltaV, Siemens, Rockwell, Schneider, Honeywell, etc.) and/or loop tuning will be viewed favorably but is not mandatory.
Job Types: Full-time, Permanent
